str2: A primary particle; but, and, etc.
If. From ei and an; a conditional particle; in case that, provided, etc.
And he, she, it, and that. From kai and ekeinos; likewise that.

parse: Verb - Present Subjunctive Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: (a) I remain, tarry, (b) I remain in, persist in. From epi and meno; to stay over, i.e. Remain.
Unbelief, unfaithfulness, distrust. From apistos; faithlessness, i.e. disbelief, or unfaithfulness.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Passive - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To graft in, ingraft. From en and a derivative of kentron; to prick in, i.e. Ingraft.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
(a) of persons: powerful, able, (b) of things: possible. From dunamai; powerful or capable; neuter possible.
To graft in, ingraft. From en and a derivative of kentron; to prick in, i.e. Ingraft.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative Masculine 3rd Person Plural
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
Probably from the same as pale; anew, i.e. back, once more, or furthermore or on the other hand.
